The paper deals with error correction for signals, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of message passing decoding is a common technique in compressed sensing (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of the approach through numerical simulations, which falls under the category of simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
